Elven Realms of Aetheria
The elves do not control a single massive continent like the humans. Instead, they inhabit Sylvandor, a large, ancient super-continent (roughly the size of South America + Australia combined) located west of Veloria across the Azure Sea. A smaller chain of elven-controlled islands lies to the south.
Total elven population across all territories: ≈ 9.4 million (very low density due to long lifespans and strict territorial control).
Elven society is heavily fragmented. There are 9 Sovereign High Forest Enclaves (more civilized, isolationist) and 4 major Wildwood Exile Territories (primal, aggressive). Most are independent, though some maintain loose alliances.
Due to the Veiling, ancient demonic wars, and constant skirmishes, elven economies are self-sufficient but declining. They suffer from low birth rates, loss of Golden Age magic, and the endless Shadow War against demons. Trade is limited and carefully controlled. Their greatest wealth lies in magical reagents, ancient artifacts, and high-quality crafts.

