General Geography & Climate of Sylvandor

Climate: Mostly temperate to subtropical, with heavy magical influence. Massive ancient forests cover ~70% of the land.
Major Features:
World Tree Heartlands – Central sacred region.
Thornveil Mountains – Eastern border with demons (heavily contested).
Starshore Coast – Western beautiful coastline with glowing coral reefs.
Northern Frostweald – Cold, ancient pine forests.

Vegetation: Colossal living trees, glowing flowers, crystal groves, and sentient plants. Many areas still show scars from ancient demonic wars (blackened or blood-red zones).

Economic Reality:

Elves are largely self-sufficient thanks to magical agriculture and long lifespans.
Constant demonic pressure (especially on Thornveil and Shadowveil) drains resources heavily.
They export high-value luxury and magical goods but import almost nothing except metals and rare minerals.
Internal trade between enclaves is limited due to old grudges. Wildwood territories often raid for resources.
